---
description: API file-structure conventions for this repo. Apply when creating/renaming/editing Go files under api/v*/. Apply when editing relevant files, and when reasoning/planning/answering questions where this rule could influence code decisions (even if matching files are not currently open).
globs: api/v*/**/*.go
alwaysApply: false
---

- Per-object files (MUST):
  - Each API object lives in its own `<object>_types.go` file
    (e.g. `manifestcheckpoint_types.go`, `domainspecificsnapshotcontroller_types.go`).
  - Keep one root object per file.

- Common files (SHOULD):
  - `doc.go` for package docs and group/version markers.
  - `register.go` for scheme registration.

- Generated files (MUST NOT edit by hand):
  - Do NOT edit `zz_generated*` files manually.
